  "text": "Association of the increased widespread frontal theta with nonresponse to antidepressant treatment was reported in several studies [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . High frontal and rostral anterior cingulate theta was found in depressed patients in a study by Arns and colleagues (2016) and associated with treatment nonresponse.",
